i have setup my conversion tracking woith clickbank but the conversions are not being reported in newsbreak ad account

It sounds like there might be an issue with the integration between ClickBank and NewsBreak. Let's go through the setup steps to ensure everything is configured correctly. 
1. Make sure you are using ClickBank Version 8.0, as Version 7.0 is no longer supported.
2. Log in to your ClickBank account and navigate to 'Vendor Settings' > 'My Site'.
3. In the 'Advanced Tool' section, click 'Edit' and ensure that you have requested access to the Instant Notification URL.
4. Set the Secret Key to 'MONETIZENEWS' and use the following Instant Notification URL: `https://business.newsbreak.com/tracking/clickbank`.
5. Don't forget to click 'TEST IPN' twice for verification and save your changes.
6. Finally, create and test your conversion flow end-to-end in NewsBreak's Event Testing Tool by selecting 'Create/Test Web Event'.
For more detailed instructions, please refer to this [ClickBank Postback setup guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/23746617571341-How-to-set-up-a-ClickBank-Postback-on-NewsBreak). If you've followed these steps and are still experiencing issues, please let me know!
I've escalated your issue to our support team, and they will reach out to you at smilanisbiz@gmail.com with more detailed troubleshooting steps. Thank you for your patience!

Hi, Iâ€™m the NewsBreak Ad Assistant. How can I help?

To optimize your ads on NewsBreak, you can focus on several key areas: 
1. **Targeting**: Use interest, demographics, and location-based targeting to reach the right audience. You can geo-target your ad to specific zip codes, cities, counties, states, or national levels.
2. **Creative Assets**: Ensure your images and videos are high-quality and engaging. Consider using the AI-Assisted Creative Tool for better results.
3. **Ad Formats**: Choose the right ad format that aligns with your advertising goals. NewsBreak offers various ad formats and placements.
4. **Performance Tracking**: Regularly monitor the performance of your ads using the reporting tools available in your account.
5. **Bidding Strategy**: Select a bidding strategy that suits your campaign objectives.
For more detailed guidance on optimizing ads, you can refer to our article on [Types of NewsBreak Ad Formats and Placements](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/20229876903053-Types-of-NewsBreak-Ad-Formats-and-Placements). Let me know if you need further assistance!
